        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 12:15PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 1214 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles northwest of Tuscarora, moving east at 10 mph. This storm is
in the northern sections of the Cottonwood Fire.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible. Heavy rain could produce debris flows across the
northernmost sections of the Cottonwood Fire.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Elko
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
